question_output: Is changing the evidence of I going to change the probability of D?
raw_model_answer: Yes. In the network the node **I** is a direct parent of **D** (the edge I → D1 and D has I as a parent in its own CPT). In other words, setting I to a particular value (or updating its evidence) will change the distribution over D, whereas if I and D were d‑separated the evidence would have no effect.
